?You need two people who know how to play. The other was Anya.? He looks at her and sighs, feels a little sad, not really sure why, ?And now you all know how to play too.? He takes his eyes off Anya and stares pointedly at the housemate, ?or do you?? putting enough expression into it to get a chuckle from the revellers, ?because, you see? That?s the the point: there?s no way to tell if everyone?s playing the same game. It?s an allegory for life.?